msgid "“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, bhikkhu yāvatā ekaṃ mahārajjaṃ ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn127:14.20"
msgid "ayaṃ imāsaṃ ubhinnaṃ cittabhāvanānaṃ mahaggatatarā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn127:14.21"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso kaccāna, yvāyaṃ bhikkhu yāvatā ekaṃ mahārajjaṃ ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati, yo cāyaṃ bhikkhu yāvatā dve vā tīṇi vā mahārajjāni ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati—"
msgstr "two or three kingdoms … "

msgctxt "mn127:14.22"
msgid "imāsaṃ ubhinnaṃ cittabhāvanānaṃ katamā cittabhāvanā mahaggatatarā”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn127:14.23"
msgid "“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, bhikkhu yāvatā dve vā tīṇi vā mahārajjāni ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn127:14.24"
msgid "ayaṃ imāsaṃ ubhinnaṃ cittabhāvanānaṃ mahaggatatarā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn127:14.25"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso kaccāna, yvāyaṃ bhikkhu yāvatā dve vā tīṇi vā mahārajjāni ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati, yo cāyaṃ bhikkhu yāvatā samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati—"
msgstr "this land surrounded by ocean?” "

msgctxt "mn127:14.26"
msgid "imāsaṃ ubhinnaṃ cittabhāvanānaṃ katamā cittabhāvanā mahaggatatarā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:14.27"
msgid "“Yvāyaṃ, bhante, bhikkhu yāvatā samuddapariyantaṃ pathaviṃ ‘mahaggatan’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati—"
msgstr "“When a mendicant meditates on this land surrounded by ocean.” "

msgctxt "mn127:14.28"
msgid "ayaṃ imāsaṃ ubhinnaṃ cittabhāvanānaṃ mahaggatatarā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:14.29"
msgid "“Ayaṃ kho, āvuso kaccāna, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena tāsaṃ devatānaṃ ekaṃ devanikāyaṃ upapannānaṃ santettha ekaccā devatā parittābhā, santi panettha ekaccā devatā appamāṇābhā”ti. "
msgstr "“This is the cause, Reverend Kaccāna, this is the reason why, when those deities have been reborn in a single order of gods, some deities there have limited radiance, while some have limitless radiance.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15, pts-vp-pli3.151, sc17
msgctxt "mn127:15.1"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante anuruddha. "
msgstr "“Good, Venerable Anuruddha! "

msgctxt "mn127:15.2"
msgid "Atthi ca me ettha uttariṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "I have a further question about this. "

#. VAR: Yāvatā → yā tā (mr)
msgctxt "mn127:15.3"
msgid "Yāvatā, bhante, devatā ābhā sabbā tā saṃkiliṭṭhābhā udāhu santettha ekaccā devatā parisuddhābhā”ti? "
msgstr "Do all the radiant deities have corrupted radiance, or do some there have pure radiance?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:15.4"
msgid "“Tadaṅgena kho, āvuso kaccāna, santettha ekaccā devatā saṃkiliṭṭhābhā, santi panettha ekaccā devatā parisuddhābhā”ti. "
msgstr "“In that respect, Reverend Kaccāna, some deities there have corrupted radiance, while some have pure radiance.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16
msgctxt "mn127:16.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, anuruddha, hetu ko paccayo, yena tāsaṃ devatānaṃ ekaṃ devanikāyaṃ upapannānaṃ santettha ekaccā devatā saṃkiliṭṭhābhā, santi panettha ekaccā devatā parisuddhābhā”ti? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, Venerable Anuruddha, what is the reason why, when those deities have been reborn in a single order of gods, some deities there have corrupted radiance, while some have pure radiance?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.152, sc18
msgctxt "mn127:16.2"
msgid "“Tena hāvuso kaccāna, upamaṃ te karissāmi. "
msgstr "“Well then, Reverend Kaccāna, I shall give you a simile. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.3"
msgid "Upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti. "
msgstr "For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso kaccāna, telappadīpassa jhāyato telampi aparisuddhaṃ vaṭṭipi aparisuddhā. "
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp was burning with impure oil and impure wick. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.5"
msgid "So telassapi aparisuddhattā vaṭṭiyāpi aparisuddhattā andhandhaṃ viya jhāyati; "
msgstr "Because of the impurity of the oil and the wick it burns dimly, as it were. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:16.6"
msgid "evameva kho, āvuso kaccāna, idhekacco bhikkhu ‘saṃkiliṭṭhābhā’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati, "
msgstr "In the same way, take some mendicant who meditates determined on pervading ‘corrupted radiance’. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.7"
msgid "tassa kāyaduṭṭhullampi na suppaṭippassaddhaṃ hoti, thinamiddhampi na susamūhataṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccampi na suppaṭivinītaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Their physical discomfort is not completely settled, their dullness and drowsiness is not completely eradicated, and their restlessness and remorse is not completely eliminated. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.8"
msgid "So kāyaduṭṭhullassapi na suppaṭippassaddhattā thinamiddhassapi na susamūhatattā uddhaccakukkuccassapi na suppaṭivinītattā andhandhaṃ viya jhāyati. "
msgstr "Because of this they practice absorption dimly, as it were. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.9"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā saṃkiliṭṭhābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of corrupted radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:16.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso kaccāna, telappadīpassa jhāyato telampi parisuddhaṃ vaṭṭipi parisuddhā. "
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp was burning with pure oil and pure wick. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.11"
msgid "So telassapi parisuddhattā vaṭṭiyāpi parisuddhattā na andhandhaṃ viya jhāyati; "
msgstr "Because of the purity of the oil and the wick it doesn’t burn dimly, as it were. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:16.12"
msgid "evameva kho, āvuso kaccāna, idhekacco bhikkhu ‘parisuddhābhā’ti pharitvā adhimuccitvā viharati. "
msgstr "In the same way, take some mendicant who meditates determined on pervading ‘pure radiance’. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.13"
msgid "Tassa kāyaduṭṭhullampi suppaṭippassaddhaṃ hoti, thinamiddhampi susamūhataṃ hoti, uddhaccakukkuccampi suppaṭivinītaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Their physical discomfort is completely settled, their dullness and drowsiness is completely eradicated, and their restlessness and remorse is completely eliminated. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.14"
msgid "So kāyaduṭṭhullassapi suppaṭippassaddhattā thinamiddhassapi susamūhatattā uddhaccakukkuccassapi suppaṭivinītattā na andhandhaṃ viya jhāyati. "
msgstr "Because of this they don’t practice absorption dimly, as it were. "

msgctxt "mn127:16.15"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā parisuddhābhānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of pure radiance. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:16.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, āvuso kaccāna, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena tāsaṃ devatānaṃ ekaṃ devanikāyaṃ upapannānaṃ santettha ekaccā devatā saṃkiliṭṭhābhā, santi panettha ekaccā devatā parisuddhābhā”ti. "
msgstr "“This is the cause, Reverend Kaccāna, this is the reason why, when those deities have been reborn in a single order of gods, some deities there have corrupted radiance, while some have pure radiance.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc19
msgctxt "mn127:17.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sabhiyo kaccāno āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Venerable Abhiya Kaccāna said to Venerable Anuruddha, "

msgctxt "mn127:17.2"
msgid "“sādhu, bhante anuruddha. "
msgstr "“Good, Venerable Anuruddha! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:17.3"
msgid "Na, bhante, āyasmā anuruddho evamāha: "
msgstr "Venerable Anuruddha, you don’t say, "

msgctxt "mn127:17.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ me sutan’ti vā ‘evaṃ arahati bhavitun’ti vā; "
msgstr "‘So I have heard’ or ‘It ought to be like this.’ "

msgctxt "mn127:17.5"
msgid "atha ca pana, bhante, āyasmā anuruddho ‘evampi tā devatā, itipi tā devatā’tveva bhāsati. "
msgstr "Rather, you say: ‘These deities are like this, those deities are like that.’ "

msgctxt "mn127:17.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "Sir, it occurs to me, "

msgctxt "mn127:17.7"
msgid "‘addhā āyasmatā anuruddhena tāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ sannivutthapubbañceva sallapitapubbañca sākacchā ca samāpajjitapubbā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Clearly, Venerable Anuruddha has previously lived together with those deities, conversed, and engaged in discussion.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn127:17.8"
msgid "“Addhā kho ayaṃ, āvuso kaccāna, āsajja upanīya vācā bhāsitā, "
msgstr "“Your words are clearly invasive and intrusive, Reverend Kaccāna. "

msgctxt "mn127:17.9"
msgid "api ca te ahaṃ byākarissāmi: "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I will answer you. "

msgctxt "mn127:17.10"
msgid "‘dīgharattaṃ kho me, āvuso kaccāna, tāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ sannivutthapubbañceva sallapitapubbañca sākacchā ca samāpajjitapubbā’”ti. "
msgstr "For a long time I have previously lived together with those deities, conversed, and engaged in discussion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, sc20
msgctxt "mn127:18.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā sabhiyo kaccāno pañcakaṅgaṃ thapatiṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Venerable Abhiya Kaccāna said to Pañcakaṅga the master builder, "

msgctxt "mn127:18.2"
msgid "“lābhā te, gahapati, suladdhaṃ te, gahapati, "
msgstr "“You’re fortunate, householder, so very fortunate, "

#. VAR: mayañcimaṃ → yampimaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: pahāsi → pajahasi (mr)
msgctxt "mn127:18.3"
msgid "yaṃ tvañceva taṃ kaṅkhādhammaṃ pahāsi, mayañcimaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ alatthamhā savanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "to have given up your state of uncertainty, and to have got the chance to listen to this exposition of the teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn127:18.4"
msgid "Anuruddhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

